cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a new architecture for neural networks that can manipulate numerical information more systematically and generalize better outside of the range of numerical values encountered during training. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents experiments involving arithmetic over images (cs.CV) and translation of numerical language (cs.CL), which further support these sub-categories.
